<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Picatti Brothers Apparel Dashboard</title>
<meta name="theme-color" content="#1f2937">
<style>
:root { --bg:#f5f7fb; --card:#fff; --line:#dbe3ee; --text:#0f172a; --muted:#64748b; --brand:#1f2937; --brand2:#374151; --accent:#f59e0b; --accent2:#0f766e; --danger:#b42318; }
* { box-sizing:border-box; }
body { margin:0; font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; background:var(--bg); color:var(--text); }
.topbar { background:linear-gradient(180deg,var(--brand),var(--brand2)); color:#fff; padding:14px 18px; position:sticky; top:0; z-index:20; box-shadow:0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.2); }
.topbar-inner { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap; max-width:1400px; margin:0 auto; }
.brand { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:14px; }
.brand img { height:54px; width:auto; border-radius:8px; background:#fff; padding:4px; }
.brand h1 { margin:0; font-size:22px; }
.brand p { margin:4px 0 0; font-size:13px; color:#dbe3ef; }
.wrap { max-width:1400px; margin:0 auto; padding:16px; }
.banner { background:#fff7e6; border:1px solid #f2d38f; border-radius:14px; padding:12px 14px; margin-bottom:14px; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; }
.pill { display:inline-block; background:#eef2ff; color:#3730a3; border-radius:999px; padding:6px 10px; font-size:12px; font-weight:700; }
.mode-demo { background:#fff1f2; border-color:#fecdd3; color:#9f1239; }
.tabs { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:14px; }
.tabbtn { border:1px solid var(--line); background:#fff; border-radius:12px; padding:10px 14px; cursor:pointer; font-weight:700; }
.tabbtn.active { background:var(--accent); border-color:var(--accent); color:#111827; }
.card { background:var(--card); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:16px; padding:14px; box-shadow:0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.04); }
.card h2, .card h3 { margin:0 0 8px; }
.sub { font-size:13px; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:12px; }
.row { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(12,1fr); gap:10px; }
.col-12 { grid-column:span 12; } .col-8 { grid-column:span 8; } .col-6 { grid-column:span 6; } .col-4 { grid-column:span 4; } .col-3 { grid-column:span 3; } .col-2 { grid-column:span 2; }
label { display:block; font-size:12px; font-weight:700; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:5px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.04em; }
input, select, button, textarea { width:100%; padding:10px 12px; border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:10px; font-size:14px; }
button { cursor:pointer; font-weight:700; }
.btn { background:var(--accent); border:none; color:#111827; }
.btn-secondary { background:#f8fafc; }
.btn-good { background:#ecfdf3; color:var(--accent2); }
.btn-danger { background:#fff1f2; color:var(--danger); }
.btn-inline { width:auto; }
.grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(255px,1fr)); gap:14px; }
.product { border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; background:#fff; }
.product img { width:100%; height:250px; object-fit:contain; background:#f8fafc; display:block; }
.product-body { padding:12px; }
.product h3 { margin:0 0 4px; font-size:17px; min-height:42px; }
.sku { color:var(--muted); font-size:12px; font-weight:700; }
.price { font-size:20px; font-weight:800; margin:8px 0 10px; }
.layout { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1.15fr .85fr; gap:16px; }
.sticky { position:sticky; top:88px; }
.summarygrid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); gap:10px; margin-bottom:12px; }
.stat { border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:12px; padding:12px; background:#fbfcfe; }
.stat .n { font-size:24px; font-weight:800; }
.notice { padding:10px 12px; border-radius:10px; margin:10px 0; font-size:13px; }
.warn { background:#fff7ed; border:1px solid #fed7aa; color:#9a3412; }
.good { background:#ecfdf3; border:1px solid #a7f3d0; color:#065f46; }
.cart-line { border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:12px; padding:10px; margin-bottom:8px; background:#fcfcfd; }
.cart-line strong { display:block; }
.right { float:right; }
.section-actions { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:10px; margin-bottom:10px; }
.section-actions > * { width:auto; }
table { width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; }
th, td { padding:10px 8px; border-bottom:1px solid var(--line); text-align:left; vertical-align:top; }
th { font-size:12px; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--muted); }
.scroll { max-height:380px; overflow:auto; }
.sheet { border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:14px; padding:14px; background:#fff; }
.order-card { border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:12px; padding:12px; background:#fbfdff; margin-bottom:10px; }
.hidden { display:none !important; }
.tiny { font-size:12px; } .muted { color:var(--muted); }
.filterbar { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:14px; }
.filterbar input, .filterbar select { max-width:240px; }
@media (max-width: 980px) {
  .layout { grid-template-columns:1fr; }
  .sticky { position:static; }
  .summarygrid { grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; }
  .col-8, .col-6, .col-4, .col-3, .col-2 { grid-column:span 12; }
}
@media print {
  .topbar, .banner, .tabs, .no-print { display:none !important; }
  body { background:#fff; }
  .card { box-shadow:none; border:none; padding:0; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="topbar">
  <div class="topbar-inner">
    <div class="brand">
      <img src="assets/picatti-logo.png" alt="Picatti Brothers">
      <div>
        <h1>Picatti Brothers Apparel System</h1>
        <p>Employee ordering plus a true employer dashboard with vendor totals, pull summaries, and employee packing slips.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="modeBadge" class="pill">Starting…</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="banner">
    <div><strong>Employees must submit exactly 7 items.</strong> Mixed sizes across shirts, hoodies, and jackets are supported. Men’s, women’s, and unisex filters are built in.</div>
    <span class="pill">Central dashboard ready</span>
  </div>

  <div class="tabs no-print">
    <button class="tabbtn active" data-tab="employeeTab" onclick="switchTab('employeeTab', this)">Employee Ordering</button>
    <button class="tabbtn" data-tab="dashboardTab" onclick="switchTab('dashboardTab', this)">Employer Dashboard</button>
    <button class="tabbtn" data-tab="setupTab" onclick="switchTab('setupTab', this)">Firebase Setup</button>
  </div>

  <div id="employeeTab">
    <div class="layout">
      <div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Shop Apparel</h2>
          <div class="sub">Employees enter their name, choose items, select color and size per item, and submit exactly 7 items.</div>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-6"><label>Employee Name</label><input id="employeeName" placeholder="Karen Smith"></div>
            <div class="col-6"><label>Department / Team</label><input id="employeeDept" placeholder="Office, Field, Sales"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="filterbar" style="margin-top:12px;">
            <input id="searchBox" placeholder="Search apparel" oninput="renderProducts()">
            <select id="audienceFilter" onchange="renderProducts()">
              <option value="">All fits</option>
              <option value="Men">Men</option>
              <option value="Women">Women</option>
              <option value="Unisex">Unisex</option>
            </select>
            <select id="categoryFilter" onchange="renderProducts()"><option value="">All categories</option></select>
          </div>
          <div id="shoppingNotice" class="notice warn">Enter employee name first, then select exactly 7 items.</div>
          <div id="productGrid" class="grid"></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="sticky">
          <div class="card">
            <h2>Employee Cart</h2>
            <div class="sub">Employee price is always $0. Vendor cost is tracked for the employer dashboard.</div>
            <div class="summarygrid">
              <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Items in Cart</div><div class="n" id="cartPieces">0</div></div>
              <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Items Still Needed</div><div class="n" id="piecesLeft">7</div></div>
              <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Vendor Cost</div><div class="n" id="cartCost">$0.00</div></div>
              <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Order Rule</div><div class="n tiny" style="font-size:18px;">Exactly 7</div></div>
            </div>
            <div id="cartLines"></div>
            <div class="section-actions no-print">
              <button class="btn-good btn-inline" onclick="submitCart()">Submit Employee Order</button>
              <button class="btn-danger btn-inline" onclick="clearCart()">Clear Cart</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card" style="margin-top:16px;">
            <h2>How this works</h2>
            <div class="sub">This version supports a real employer dashboard when Firebase is connected.</div>
            <div class="tiny muted">
              1. Employees submit orders from their phones.<br>
              2. Orders sync into one shared database.<br>
              3. Employer dashboard shows vendor totals and printable packing reports.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="dashboardTab" class="hidden">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Employer Dashboard</h2>
      <div class="sub">Live vendor totals, all employee orders, print tools, and CSV exports.</div>
      <div class="summarygrid">
        <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Employees</div><div class="n" id="sumEmployees">0</div></div>
        <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Orders</div><div class="n" id="sumOrders">0</div></div>
        <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Total Items</div><div class="n" id="sumPieces">0</div></div>
        <div class="stat"><div class="tiny muted">Vendor Total</div><div class="n" id="sumCost">$0.00</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-actions no-print">
        <button class="btn-secondary btn-inline" onclick="exportVendorTotals()">Export Vendor Totals CSV</button>
        <button class="btn-secondary btn-inline" onclick="exportEmployeeOrders()">Export Employee Orders CSV</button>
        <button class="btn-secondary btn-inline" onclick="printAllEmployeeSheets()">Print All Employee Sheets</button>
        <button class="btn-secondary btn-inline" onclick="printPullSummary()">Print Pull Summary</button>
        <button class="btn-danger btn-inline" onclick="clearAllOrders()">Clear All Orders</button>
      </div>

      <div class="layout">
        <div>
          <div class="sheet">
            <strong>Vendor Order Totals</strong>
            <div class="tiny muted" style="margin:4px 0 10px;">Grouped by item, color, size, and total quantity.</div>
            <div class="scroll">
              <table id="vendorTotalsTable">
                <thead><tr><th>SKU</th><th>Item</th><th>Color</th><th>Size</th><th>Qty</th><th>Cost</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody></tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="sheet">
            <strong>Employee Orders</strong>
            <div class="tiny muted" style="margin:4px 0 10px;">Every order visible in one place for the employer.</div>
            <div id="ordersList" class="scroll"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="setupTab" class="hidden">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Firebase Setup</h2>
      <div class="sub">The app works in demo mode immediately. To make it multi-user and shared across employee phones, paste your Firebase web config below and deploy to Firebase Hosting.</div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <label>Firebase Web Config JSON</label>
          <textarea id="firebaseConfigInput" rows="8" placeholder='{"apiKey":"...","authDomain":"...","projectId":"...","storageBucket":"...","messagingSenderId":"...","appId":"..."}'></textarea>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="section-actions">
        <button class="btn btn-inline" onclick="saveFirebaseConfig()">Save Firebase Config</button>
        <button class="btn-secondary btn-inline" onclick="loadSavedFirebaseConfig()">Reload Saved Config</button>
      </div>
      <div id="setupStatus" class="notice warn">No Firebase config saved yet. The app is currently in single-device demo mode.</div>
      <div class="tiny muted">
        Once Firebase is connected, employee orders sync live into one employer dashboard. Deploy these files with Firebase Hosting for a real shared link.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

